LongDescription: Amit Varma is a writer and podcaster based in Mumbai. In 2008, his first novel My friend, Sancho was nominated to the longlist for the Man Asian Literary Prize 2008. , '\n\xa0']

Name: Shweta Tripathi
LongDescription:
['Shweta Tripathi Sharma is a popular Actor, known for the character of Golu Gupta in Mirzapur. She began her film career as a production assistant and associate director and gained wider recognition and accolades for her acting performances in films/series like Masaan, Gone Kesh, Ye Kaali Kaali Ankhein, Laakhon Mein Ek and many more.',
, '\n',
, '\nYou can check out her episode on Chalchitra Talks\xa0', here, '.']

Name: Rahul Dua
LongDescription:
["Rahul Dua is a stand-up comedian and is referred to as the brightest comic of the new generation. He got his first big break when he appeared on 'Comicstaan', a comedy reality show. He is also an active YouTuber and his genre of comedy is 'observational comedy'. Dua was an investment banker, who turned into a standup comedian.",
, '\n\xa0']

Name: Gajraj Rao
LongDescription: Gajraj Rao is an Indian actor who appears predominantly in Hindi films. He is known most for his award-winning performance in Badhaai Ho. He debuted in 1994 with a minor role in Shekhar Kapur's Bandit Queen and has since worked in many films and web series.

, '\n\xa0']

Name: Nucleya
LongDescription:
["Udyan Sagar, better known by his stage name Nucleya is a bass-heavy electronics artist based in New Delhi. In 1998 he co-founded Bandish Projekt with Mayur Narvekar and Mehirr Nath Choppra before leaving it in 2007. In 2013 he released his first all-original EP 'Koocha Monster', which was followed by Bass Rani. Most recently he worked with Ritviz on the album 'Baaraat' which was released in 2021. Nucleya has also been a judge in MTV Hustle.",
, '\n\xa0']

Name: Joe Dunthorne
LongDescription:
["Joe Dunthorne is a Welsh novelist, poet, and journalist. He first made his name with his novel Submarine, which was made into a film in 2010. Dunthorne's second novel, Wild Abandon went on to win the Royal Society of Literature's Encore Award for Best Second Novel. His latest novel, The Adulterants was published in 2018.",
, '\n',
, '\nYou can check out his episode on Chalchitra Talks\xa0', here, '.']
